==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fermium
<hw>fermium</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the transuranic element of atomic
number 100; symbol Fm. The atomic weight of the most stable isotope,
having a half-life of about 80 days, is 257. The first isotope,
Fm<sup>255</sup> was discovered in 1952 in the debris of a thermonuclear
explosion. Other istopes have been produced in nuclear reactors and by
decay of other transuranic elements.</def> <au>Handb. Ch. Phys.
61.</au>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Fm.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

